   323â†’## [0.4.0] - 2017-12-24
   324â†’
   325â†’The changes in this release include cleanup of some obscure functionality and a more robust public
   326â†’API designed to support bridges to other logging systems, and provide more flexibility to new
   327â†’features in the future.
   329â†’### Compatibility
   330â†’
   331â†’Vast portions of the Rust ecosystem use the 0.3.x release series of log, and we don't want to force
   332â†’the community to go through the pain of upgrading every crate to 0.4.x at the exact same time. Along
   333â†’with 0.4.0, we've published a new 0.3.9 release which acts as a "shim" over 0.4.0. This will allow
   334â†’crates using either version to coexist without losing messages from one side or the other.
   345â†’### New
   346â†’
   347â†’* The crate is now `no_std` by default.
   348â†’* `Level` and `LevelFilter` now implement `Serialize` and `Deserialize` when the `serde` feature is
   349â†’    enabled.
   350â†’* The `Record` and `Metadata` types can now be constructed by third-party code via a builder API.
   351â†’* The `logger` free function returns a reference to the logger implementation. This, along with the
   352â†’    ability to construct `Record`s, makes it possible to bridge from another logging framework to
   353â†’    this one without digging into the private internals of the crate. The standard `error!` `warn!`,
   354â†’    etc., macros now exclusively use the public API of the crate rather than "secret" internal APIs.
   355â†’* `Log::flush` has been added to allow crates to tell the logging implementation to ensure that all
   356â†’    "in flight" log events have been persisted. This can be used, for example, just before an
   357â†’    application exits to ensure that asynchronous log sinks finish their work.
   359â†’### Removed
   360â†’
   361â†’* The `shutdown` and `shutdown_raw` functions have been removed. Supporting shutdown significantly
   362â†’    complicated the implementation and imposed a performance cost on each logging operation.
   363â†’* The `log_panics` function and its associated `nightly` Cargo feature have been removed. Use the
   364â†’    [log-panics](https://crates.io/crates/log-panics) instead.
   366â†’### Changed
   367â†’
   368â†’* The `Log` prefix has been removed from type names. For example, `LogLevelFilter` is now
   369â†’    `LevelFilter`, and `LogRecord` is now `Record`.
   370â†’* The `MaxLogLevelFilter` object has been removed in favor of a `set_max_level` free function.
   371â†’* The `set_logger` free functions have been restructured. The logger is now directly passed to the
   372â†’    functions rather than a closure which returns the logger. `set_logger` now takes a `&'static
   373â†’    Log` and is usable in `no_std` contexts in place of the old `set_logger_raw`. `set_boxed_logger`
   374â†’    is a convenience function which takes a `Box<Log>` but otherwise acts like `set_logger`. It
   375â†’    requires the `std` feature.
   376â†’* The `file` and `module_path` values in `Record` no longer have the `'static` lifetime to support
   377â†’    integration with other logging frameworks that don't provide a `'static` lifetime for the
   378â†’    equivalent values.
   379â†’* The `file`, `line`, and `module_path` values in `Record` are now `Option`s to support integration
   380â†’    with other logging frameworks that don't provide those values.
   382â†’### In the Future
   383â†’
   384â†’* We're looking to add support for *structured* logging - the inclusion of extra key-value pairs of
   385â†’    information in a log event in addition to the normal string message. This should be able to be
   386â†’    added in a backwards compatible manner to the 0.4.x series when the design is worked out.
   388â†’## Older
   389â†’
   390â†’Look at the [release tags] for information about older releases.
